           <div itemprop="articleBody">
             
  <div class="section" id="installing-ansible">
<span id="intro-installation-guide"></span><span id="installation-guide"></span><h1>Installing Ansible<a class="headerlink" href="#installing-ansible" title="Permalink to this headline"></a></h1>
<p>Ansible is an agentless automation tool that you install on a control node. From the control node, Ansible manages machines and other devices remotely (by default, over the SSH protocol).</p>
<p>To install Ansible for use at the command line, simply install the Ansible package on one machine (which could easily be a laptop). You do not need to install a database or run any daemons. Ansible can manage an entire fleet of remote machines from that one control node.</p>
<div class="contents local topic" id="contents">
<ul class="simple">
<li><p><a class="reference internal" href="#prerequisites" id="id7">Prerequisites</a></p>
<ul>
<li><p><a class="reference internal" href="#control-node-requirements" id="id8">Control node requirements</a></p></li>
<li><p><a class="reference internal" href="#managed-node-requirements" id="id9">Managed node requirements</a></p></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><p><a class="reference internal" href="#selecting-an-ansible-artifact-and-version-to-install" id="id10">Selecting an Ansible artifact and version to install</a></p>
<ul>
<li><p><a class="reference internal" href="#installing-the-ansible-community-package" id="id11">Installing the Ansible community package</a></p></li>
<li><p><a class="reference internal" href="#installing-ansible-core" id="id12">Installing <cite>ansible-core</cite></a></p></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><p><a class="reference internal" href="#installing-and-upgrading-ansible-with-pip" id="id13">Installing and upgrading Ansible with <code class="docutils literal notranslate"><span class="pre">pip</span></code></a></p>
<ul>
<li><p><a class="reference internal" href="#prerequisites-installing-pip" id="id14">Prerequisites: Installing <code class="docutils literal notranslate"><span class="pre">pip</span></code></a></p></li>
<li><p><a class="reference internal" href="#installing-ansible-with-pip" id="id15">Installing Ansible with <code class="docutils literal notranslate"><span class="pre">pip</span></code></a></p></li>
<li><p><a class="reference internal" href="#installing-ansible-in-a-virtual-environment-with-pip" id="id16">Installing Ansible in a virtual environment with <code class="docutils literal notranslate"><span class="pre">pip</span></code></a></p></li>
<li><p><a class="reference internal" href="#upgrading-ansible-with-pip" id="id17">Upgrading Ansible with <code class="docutils literal notranslate"><span class="pre">pip</span></code></a></p>
<ul>
